16. Transactions
Purpose

Ensures all operations succeed or fail together.

Methods:

setAutoCommit(false)

commit()

rollback()

Example:

Bank money transfer.

17. Auto Commit

Default:

true

Every SQL statement is committed automatically.

Disable:

con.setAutoCommit(false);

18. Batch Processing

Purpose:

Execute multiple SQL statements together.
Improves performance.

Methods:

addBatch()

executeBatch()

19. try-with-resources

Automatically closes:

Connection
Statement
ResultSet

Preferred over manually closing resources.

20. Connection Pooling

Instead of creating a new connection every time:

Request
     ↓
Borrow Connection
     ↓
Use
     ↓
Return to Pool

Advantages:

Faster
Better performance
Less memory usage

Examples:

HikariCP
Apache DBCP
C3P0


21. Common Exceptions
SQLException

Reasons:
Wrong URL
Wrong Username
Wrong Password
SQL Syntax Error
Database not running

22. Best Practices
Use PreparedStatement.
Use try-with-resources.
Close database resources.
Use transactions for multiple related operations.
Use batch processing for bulk inserts.
Never hardcode credentials.
Use connection pooling in production.

